text:
Washington Street, west side, from Morton Street to West 10th (formerly Amos) Street, prior to the demolition of the buildings. The building on the S.W. corner of Barrow Street is St. Veronica's Parochial School.

July 25, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

Washington Street, north from Morton Street, showing a clearance on the west side of this thoroughfare and opposite same the U. S. Government Building known as the U. S. Appraisers Stores.

This 10 story structure bears No. 641 Washington Street, occupying the entire block bounded by Barrow, Christopher and Greenwich Streets. View No. 2 is taken mainly to show this building.

December 3, 1931
View 1 and 2

text:
Washington Street, south from Morton Street, showing a W.P. A. street car track removal project. At the right is the St. John's Park Freight Terminal terminating at Clarkson Street. Extending from same is the elevated roadbed of the New York Central Railroad.

April 28, 1937

W.P. A. Photo
Five Boroughs Project
